---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';

const refs = [
  {
    title: 'Securing Elliptic Curve Cryptocurrencies against Quantum Vulnerabilities',
    authors: 'Babbush, Zalcman, Gidney et al. (Google Quantum AI, 2026)',
    href: 'https://quantumai.google/static/site-assets/downloads/cryptocurrency-whitepaper.pdf',
  },
  {
    title: 'How to compute a 256-bit elliptic curve private key with only 50 million Toffoli gates',
    authors: 'D. Litinski (2023)',
    href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/2306.08585',
  },
  {
    title: 'Quantum resource estimates for computing elliptic curve discrete logarithms',
    authors: 'M. Roetteler et al. (ASIACRYPT 2017)',
    href: 'https://eprint.iacr.org/2017/598',
  },
  {
    title: 'On the Size of Pairing-based Non-interactive Arguments',
    authors: 'J. Groth (2016)',
    href: 'https://eprint.iacr.org/2016/260',
  },
  {
    title: 'A new quantum ripple-carry addition circuit',
    authors: 'S. Cuccaro et al. (2004)',
    href: 'https://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0410184',
  },
  {
    title: 'SP1 zkVM',
    authors: 'Succinct Labs',
    href: 'https://github.com/succinctlabs/sp1',
  },
];
---

<Base
  title="About — Quantum Proof"
  description="What this project is, why we built it, and the references behind every claim."
>
  <div class="container-prose py-14">
    <span class="section-eyebrow">About</span>
    <h1 class="mt-3 max-w-3xl text-4xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-slate-900 sm:text-5xl dark:text-white">
      Why this exists
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-5 max-w-2xl text-lg leading-relaxed text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300">
      Google Quantum AI's March 2026 whitepaper compressed the cost of breaking secp256k1 into
      a regime that is now researchable. The framework should be too. <strong>quantum_proof</strong>
      pairs an educational explainer with a working open-source implementation so the community
      can independently study, verify, and extend the result.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-doc mt-10 max-w-3xl">
      <h2>Two halves of one project</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>The explainer.</strong> Originally a single static page; now a multi-route SPA
          covering the threat model, the verification pipeline, the historical context, and the
          interactive resource calculators.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>The framework.</strong> <a href="/oathbreaker">Oathbreaker</a> — a complete
          reversible Shor's ECDLP implementation in Rust, with measured Oath-8/16/32 results, a
          NISQ Qiskit POC, SageMath SEA curve verification, and an SP1 Groth16 proof pipeline.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Why open it up?</h2>
      <p>
        Withheld circuits cannot be examined for subtle bugs, optimization opportunities, or
        downstream uses (post-quantum migration tooling, NIST-style benchmarks, hardware
        commissioning). Open analogues like Oathbreaker fill that gap without publishing
        attack-grade circuits at cryptographic scale.
      </p>

      <h2>Disclaimer</h2>
      <p>
        This repository is an independent educational and research resource. It is not affiliated
        with or endorsed by Google Quantum AI. The educational content is based on the
        publicly-available whitepaper linked in the references. Oath curves are toy curves
        (≤64-bit fields, ≤32-bit security) intended for software verification, hardware
        benchmarking, and pedagogy — not as cryptographic primitives.
      </p>

      <h2>License</h2>
      <p>MIT — see <a href="https://github.com/chippr-robotics/quantum_proof/blob/main/oathbreaker/LICENSE" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LICENSE</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="bg-brand-50/60 py-14 dark:bg-slate-900/40">
    <div class="container-prose">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">References</span>
      <h2 class="section-title mt-3">Sources behind the claims</h2>

      <ul class="mt-8 space-y-3">
        {refs.map((r) => (
          <li class="card card-hover reveal">
            <a class="font-semibold text-brand-700 hover:text-brand-800 dark:text-brand-300" href={r.href} target="_blank" rel="noopener">
              {r.title} ↗
            </a>
            <p class="mt-1 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400">{r.authors}</p>
          </li>
        ))}
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
